comment.author: 32162360@N00
comment._content: I think it is a Morris Cowley, after 1926. Previous models had the famous 'bull-nose' - see en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Morris_Cowley#Morris_Cowley_.281926.29 Close inspection of the radiator badge reveals "MORRIS COWLEY".

comment._content: [http://www.flickr.com/photos/beachcomberaustralia] It seems that until 1930 car registrations fell within the relm of NSW Police, and after to Dept Road Transport & Tramways. Either way it'll be a trip out to the NSW State records!
